# 🎃 Windows 11 Setup - FIXED!

## ✅ Issue Resolved

The `lightningcss` error has been fixed! I've downgraded from Tailwind CSS v4 to **Tailwind CSS v3** which is more stable and doesn't require native Windows binaries.

## 🚀 How to Run on Windows 11

### 1. Open Command Prompt or PowerShell

Press `Win + R`, type `cmd` or `powershell`, press Enter.

### 2. Navigate to Project Folder

```cmd
cd C:\Users\asumm\Downloads\0199e9e3-420d-752c-a4d5-17d36227cab1-op7W4A-Auas7-2025-10-16-14-36
```

### 3. Install Dependencies

```cmd
npm install
```

This will install all packages (should complete without errors now!).

### 4. Run Development Server

```cmd
npm run dev
```

### 5. Open in Browser

Go to **http://localhost:3000** 🎃

